16:51.924 --> 16:53.707
Listen, people are weird, man.

16:53.907 --> 16:54.668
They're just weird.

16:55.890 --> 17:01.138
And if you're gonna be insist on it going your way, there's not gonna be any shalom.

17:01.666 --> 17:02.327
You see what I'm saying?

17:02.527 --> 17:05.249
You have to create some space and let people do the weir.

17:05.530 --> 17:06.571
Let them one up you.

17:06.811 --> 17:08.012
Let them one up you.

17:08.032 --> 17:09.093
They're going to do it anyway.

17:09.113 --> 17:13.377
I say, yeah, Uncle Joe, he's always got one better.

17:14.678 --> 17:15.279
Let him do it.

17:15.419 --> 17:16.200
Don't get frustrated.

17:18.142 --> 17:19.763
You know, so-and-so always shows up with a hangover.

17:19.823 --> 17:21.505
They drink one too many drinks.

17:21.785 --> 17:24.308
That's what they're going to do.

17:24.328 --> 17:28.111
Now, I'm not talking about giving people license to abuse others.

17:29.052 --> 17:30.093
That's a different story.

17:30.113 --> 17:30.994
That's crossing a line.

17:31.522 --> 17:32.844
I'm not saying make room for that.

17:33.184 --> 17:34.566
I am saying make room for the faults.

17:35.427 --> 17:35.967
How do we do that?

17:35.988 --> 17:37.790
Well, we have to develop the attitude of Christ.

17:38.791 --> 17:40.834
We have to think unselfishly.

17:40.874 --> 17:42.496
Listen to what Paul says in Philippians 2.

17:42.956 --> 17:43.697
Don't be selfish.

17:43.777 --> 17:44.858
Don't try to impress others.

17:44.899 --> 17:45.459
Be humble.

17:45.519 --> 17:47.101
Thinking of others is better than yourselves.

17:47.502 --> 17:48.123
What if he did that?

17:48.143 --> 17:49.845
What if he thought of others as better than yourself?

17:49.865 --> 17:51.507
Wouldn't you give them some space to be weird?

17:52.228 --> 17:52.628
Yes or no?

17:53.569 --> 17:55.592
Yeah, if they're better than he's like, hey, dude, that's what you do.

17:55.752 --> 17:56.533
I'm going to let you be you.

17:57.714 --> 17:58.756
I'm not going to speak to that.

17:58.856 --> 18:00.658
I'm not going to expect it different.

18:00.962 --> 18:02.304
And he takes it a step further.

18:02.324 --> 18:03.126
Watch what Paul says here.

18:03.426 --> 18:07.913
Don't look out for your own interests the way you would like it to go, but take interest in others as well.

18:07.993 --> 18:08.554
How do we do that?

18:08.574 --> 18:08.995
Watch this.

18:09.816 --> 18:13.102
He says you must have the same attitude that Christ Jesus had.

18:14.424 --> 18:16.207
Who took on the form of a servant.

18:16.327 --> 18:26.003
Instead of leveraging equality with God, he would go on to say he took on the form of a man and he humbled himself and became obedient even to the point of death on a cross.

18:26.303 --> 18:27.986
Here's what Jesus did for you and I.

18:28.354 --> 18:29.896
He put us above himself.

18:29.976 --> 18:31.739
He put his needs above his own.

18:33.101 --> 18:34.663
And he served us by dying in the cross.

18:34.764 --> 18:37.788
Surely if Christ did that for us, you could do that for your family, yes?

18:39.350 --> 18:52.310
Many years ago, I recognized that my wife's side of the family, when we're getting together for a big meal, whether it's Thanksgiving or Christmas, we cook the beautiful meals with casseroles and all kinds of side dishes and usually a beautiful piece of meat or whatever.

18:53.492 --> 18:57.778
And when it all comes out of the oven, I remember when years ago, I was ready to eat.

18:58.274 --> 19:01.879
You know, because in New York as soon as it comes out, you know, you eat.

19:03.641 --> 19:05.263
Not my wife's side of the family.

19:05.283 --> 19:05.864
They just chill.

19:06.044 --> 19:06.585
It's kind of chill.

19:06.605 --> 19:17.440
Like it comes out, this dish comes out, that dish comes out, it sits around, you know, we say, hey, dinner's out, you know, and it takes about 15 minutes for everybody to come from upstairs and downstairs and who's taking a walk and who's in the bathroom.

19:17.460 --> 19:19.302
It's like, hey, do you know the food's ready?

19:20.804 --> 19:22.266
Nope, no urgency.

19:22.627 --> 19:27.954
So by the time everybody gets around the table, you know, we're sitting down, it's all 15 of us or 17 of us, however many there are.

19:28.066 --> 19:29.108
You know, what happens to the food?

19:30.049 --> 19:30.590
It's gotten what?

19:31.451 --> 19:31.932
It's gotten cold.

19:32.052 --> 19:35.057
It's juiced to drive me nuts.

19:35.077 --> 19:36.159
It's like, what's the matter with you people?

19:36.560 --> 19:37.561
You guys are weird.

19:39.264 --> 19:40.987
The food was was hot.

19:41.848 --> 19:42.529
Now it's not.

19:44.552 --> 19:45.294
So here's what I had to do.

19:45.314 --> 19:45.975
It's like, it's OK.

19:45.995 --> 19:47.677
I'm going to make allowance.

19:47.758 --> 19:49.600
If I really want my food hot, I'm going to make my plate.

19:49.621 --> 19:50.121
What am I going to do?

19:50.262 --> 19:51.383
I'm going to do what you have to do.

19:51.443 --> 19:53.787
I'm going to take it over to the microwave and heat it up.

19:54.508 --> 19:55.570
And that's OK.

19:55.938 --> 19:57.200
because it doesn't have to go my way.

19:57.500 --> 19:58.362
So they're shallow.

19:58.502 --> 19:59.083
See how that works?

19:59.363 --> 20:03.530
That's just a small example, small example of what we have to do.

20:03.550 --> 20:04.792
We have to be flexible.

20:05.133 --> 20:05.573
Yes or no?

20:06.114 --> 20:08.819
We gotta be a peacemaker and then we have to be flexible.

20:08.839 --> 20:09.940
Let me give you this third idea.

20:10.481 --> 20:12.344
We have to recognize that now is not the time.

20:12.424 --> 20:14.287
Listen, now is not the time.

20:14.327 --> 20:15.088
What do I mean by that?

20:15.429 --> 20:17.292
Your family is dysfunctional.

20:17.312 --> 20:18.274
You wanna know how I know that?

20:18.454 --> 20:20.317
Because my family's dysfunctional, okay?

20:20.858 --> 20:23.602
Because everybody's got some things that are not working right.

20:23.874 --> 20:26.737
And there's also some brokenness that needs to be healed.

20:27.919 --> 20:33.406
And it needs to be addressed, and it needs to be talked about just not over the Christmas gathering.

20:34.507 --> 20:37.170
Now is not the time.

20:37.490 --> 20:38.091
Does that make sense?

20:38.111 --> 20:38.712
There is a time.

20:38.952 --> 20:43.638
It's just not at Christmas to deal with the dysfunction and the brokenness.

20:43.658 --> 20:53.650
Now, I understand why people do this at their family gathering, because here's the thinking, ready, well, you know, this has been building up, and I'm gonna talk to him about this, and I'm upset about it, and you know, where everybody's gonna be there.

20:53.986 --> 20:59.534
Might as well bring it up at the Christmas dinner, you know, why he does this and why they do that and why she can't get it together.

20:59.574 --> 21:01.757
And this, I'm going to talk to them about it.

21:01.777 --> 21:05.742
After all, you know, Grandpa's going to be there and Aunt Sue's going to be there.

21:05.762 --> 21:08.626
I'm going to have like people to support me when I start bringing it up.

21:08.906 --> 21:10.388
So might as well, you know, gang up.

21:12.191 --> 21:12.892
And it makes sense.

21:15.095 --> 21:16.176
But not if you want Shalom.

21:17.558 --> 21:18.379
Not if you want peace.

21:18.740 --> 21:23.186
Proverbs, chapter 29 verse 11 says this, fools vent their anger.

21:23.330 --> 21:24.872
Say whatever they want to say.

21:25.192 --> 21:26.213
Whenever they want to say it.

21:27.375 --> 21:29.257
But the wise quietly do what?

21:29.297 --> 21:29.737
What do they do?

21:30.498 --> 21:31.239
They hold it back.

21:31.640 --> 21:32.601
Now is not the time.

21:33.962 --> 21:40.510
You say, well, if we're not going to talk about our problems over the Christmas dinner, then what the heck are we going to talk about?

21:43.894 --> 21:46.297
Ephesians chapter 4, Paul gives us this instruction.

21:46.357 --> 21:48.039
Don't use foul or abusive language.

21:48.059 --> 21:50.962
Let everything you say be good and helpful.

21:51.874 --> 21:56.520
Let it be positive wise so that your words will be an encouragement to those who hear them.

21:57.821 --> 22:02.688
So if you don't have that something positive and helpful to say to your family members, just don't say it.

22:03.529 --> 22:04.550
Just don't talk about it.

22:04.970 --> 22:05.771
Talk about sports.

22:05.831 --> 22:07.413
Talk about something neutral.

22:09.055 --> 22:10.938
Somebody like, well, I don't think I can do that.

22:11.879 --> 22:13.121
I've got too much dysfunction.

22:13.161 --> 22:14.823
We've got too much brokenness.

22:15.804 --> 22:18.347
Well, I have a little prayer for you, okay?

22:18.367 --> 22:20.690
Psalm 141, watch this little prayer.

22:21.474 --> 22:24.659
Set a guard, oh Lord, over my yapper.

22:26.121 --> 22:34.753
Just lock in key, just throw the key out, keep watch over the, help me to keep my big fat mouth shut.

22:34.793 --> 22:36.876
That's what translation, that's what the Hebrew says right there.

22:40.782 --> 22:49.554
You just need to pray, if you can't say anything positive, just pray that prayer, Lord, set a guard over my mouth, put a door over, over my lips.

22:50.306 --> 22:51.468
Can you say this with me together?

22:51.488 --> 22:53.952
Now is not the time.

22:53.992 --> 22:54.714
Can you say that with me?

22:55.235 --> 22:57.018
Now is not the time.

22:57.098 --> 23:04.010
One more time, all of our campus says, now is not the time to address your family dysfunction and brokenness.

23:05.493 --> 23:06.094
There is a time.

23:07.616 --> 23:13.106
You need to call a third party, you need to get a counselor involved, and you need to set a date for January.

23:14.914 --> 23:19.759
And you need to talk about the brokenness and the dysfunction of your family, just not over the Christmas dinner.

23:19.979 --> 23:20.359
Make sense?

23:20.379 --> 23:20.780
Yes or no?

23:21.440 --> 23:22.341
I'm just talking about Shalom.

23:22.481 --> 23:23.482
Like, you don't have to do this stuff.

23:23.502 --> 23:24.403
This is just stuff we do.

23:24.824 --> 23:25.444
What we try to do?

23:26.205 --> 23:26.645
Because why?

23:26.685 --> 23:29.208
We want Shalom over the Christmas holiday.

23:30.008 --> 23:30.929
Let me give you this fourth one.

23:31.650 --> 23:33.332
You got to forgive the offenders ahead of time.

23:33.352 --> 23:35.994
You got to forgive the offender ahead of time.

23:38.917 --> 23:42.821
In Colossians chapter 3, Paul says, make allowance for each other's weirdness.

23:42.901 --> 23:44.082
They're false, right?

23:44.834 --> 23:47.677
And then he follows that statement up with this statement.

23:48.658 --> 23:52.603
And also forgive those who have offended you.

23:52.663 --> 23:55.246
See, faults are different from offenses.

23:55.907 --> 23:59.070
False is just stuff that people just, you know, we already talked about this.

23:59.150 --> 24:01.093
It's the odd things that they do.

24:01.153 --> 24:02.274
You just gotta make space for it.

24:02.294 --> 24:03.195
You gotta be okay with it.

24:03.215 --> 24:04.016
You gotta accept it.

24:04.757 --> 24:07.099
Offenses, those are things that they've done wrong to you.

24:08.341 --> 24:12.946
So going into this Christmas season, you have to enter in forgiving

24:13.186 --> 24:18.192
People before the event, the family gathering, the Christmas season even happens.

24:21.536 --> 24:26.603
See, a lot of us have this tendency to think that the reason I don't have peace is because of the person who's hurt me.

24:27.804 --> 24:28.605
We really believe that.

24:29.486 --> 24:30.648
And it's natural to feel that way.

24:30.688 --> 24:32.971
The reason I'm hurt is because they did such and such.

24:33.031 --> 24:34.473
He said this, they did this, whatever.

24:35.634 --> 24:37.016
But that's actually not true.

24:38.838 --> 24:42.002
The person who offended you is not the source of your

24:42.210 --> 24:43.792
pain or your lack of peace.

24:43.812 --> 24:44.413
You know who is?

24:46.096 --> 24:46.556
You are.

24:48.639 --> 24:48.940
You are.

24:49.020 --> 24:52.104
You are stealing peace from yourself by holding a grudge.

24:54.267 --> 25:01.317
You are stealing shalom from yourself by harboring bitterness in your heart towards the person who offended you.

25:01.337 --> 25:02.499
They've moved on with their life.

25:02.839 --> 25:03.921
This is powerful.

25:04.402 --> 25:06.605
The person who has offended you, they're living.

25:06.625 --> 25:07.506
They're gone.

25:08.002 --> 25:09.945
Even if it's a family member, they're doing their stuff.

25:09.965 --> 25:11.407
They're not thinking about what they did to you.

25:11.748 --> 25:13.851
And here you are, you're mulling over.

25:13.911 --> 25:17.015
I can't believe, I can't believe bitterness, resentment.

25:17.376 --> 25:22.724
You're stealing peace from yourself, which is why forgiveness is really a gift to you.

25:22.784 --> 25:26.770
It's not a gift to them while I've forgiven you, like you're blessing them.

25:26.830 --> 25:27.491
No, I don't care.

25:27.511 --> 25:30.476
It's like, oh, sometimes they're even surprised.

25:30.496 --> 25:31.737
Well, I didn't know I did anything to you.

25:31.757 --> 25:32.238
Oh, thank you.

25:32.919 --> 25:34.802
Forgiveness isn't for the offender.

25:35.426 --> 25:37.088
Forgiveness is for you.

25:37.168 --> 25:42.673
You are setting yourself free from the bondage of resentment and anger and bitterness.

25:43.374 --> 25:47.457
You're stealing peace from yourself when you fail to forgive.

25:47.497 --> 25:55.245
So Paul says, hey, before the Christmas break, before the Christmas holiday, forgive ahead of time.

25:55.305 --> 26:04.914
Now, I realized that the reason some of us struggle with this so intensely is because we feel like, well, if I forgive that person, then it's like I'm saying it's okay and it didn't happen and it didn't hurt.

26:05.570 --> 26:06.751
Wrong, wrong, wrong.

26:07.852 --> 26:10.855
Forgiveness is not saying it didn't happen, it's okay, and it didn't hurt.

26:12.136 --> 26:15.359
It did happen, it wasn't okay, and it was very painful.

26:16.501 --> 26:21.946
Forgiveness is simply saying, you don't owe me anymore.

26:21.966 --> 26:31.415
It did happen, you shouldn't have done it, it was very painful, it hurt, but I'm not gonna hold it against you anymore.

26:33.217 --> 26:34.578
And then you find yourself

26:35.842 --> 26:40.347
set free from bitterness, anger, and resentment.

26:40.588 --> 26:43.792
And then you can go into the holiday and there can be peace.

26:43.812 --> 26:44.933
There can be some shalom.

26:46.255 --> 26:51.301
Now I realize even after saying that myself included, it's like, well, that's, I believe that, but it's still really hard.

26:51.961 --> 26:53.403
I still don't know if I could drop the charges.

26:53.463 --> 26:54.725
I still don't know if I can let it go.

26:54.765 --> 26:58.990
I still, and that's why Paul adds this next statement.

26:59.390 --> 27:00.752
So powerful, so insightful.

27:00.812 --> 27:02.354
God knew we would struggle with this.

27:03.138 --> 27:05.381
Remember, if you're struggling, it's like right here.

27:05.402 --> 27:12.793
It's almost like, remember, hey, hey, if this isn't easy for you, this teaching on forgiveness, remember that the Lord forgave who?

27:13.414 --> 27:13.734
You.

27:14.736 --> 27:16.539
Remember how God has dealt with you.

27:16.899 --> 27:18.742
Remember the grace that you've received.

27:19.123 --> 27:27.856
Remember all of the sin that he's forgiven you of, that mountain, that gigantic mountain of sin that he's canceled on your behalf.

27:28.798 --> 27:29.739
Remember that.

27:30.841 --> 27:31.602
And then,

27:32.002 --> 27:33.344
go and forgive the person.

27:34.186 --> 27:34.506
Oh, wow.

27:34.526 --> 27:51.834
See, this is how I've been able to forgive people in my life, just simply by taking some time to reflect and remember on the mountain of sin that God has forgiven me, all the cheating and the lying and the stealing and the pride and the lust.

27:51.894 --> 27:54.258
And you go down the list, boom, boom, boom, boom, boom.

27:57.378 --> 28:02.285
The amount of sin that I have to forgive others doesn't even compare to the mountain of sin that God has forgiven me.

28:02.325 --> 28:02.545
Yes?

28:04.728 --> 28:14.301
If you put it on scales, it's like my sin that God forgave me is so much heavier than anything I would ever have to forgive anybody else.

28:16.184 --> 28:23.994
So he says, remember, take a walk down memory lane and review the grace that you've received, and you will find it easier to forgive the people in your life.

28:24.035 --> 28:26.578
Those who've received grace and they're aware of it,

28:26.818 --> 28:29.883
are able to show grace to others.

28:31.465 --> 28:33.468
Forgive offenders ahead of time.

28:33.609 --> 28:37.174
Now, what that also means, this is really insightful, okay?

28:38.957 --> 28:44.826
Forgiveness ahead of time means not just for past things that have been done, but also sins that are gonna happen at the Christmas gathering.

28:47.510 --> 28:50.094
Like somebody's gonna say something is hurtful, somebody's gonna do something.

28:52.077 --> 28:55.282
You don't even know what it is, hasn't even happened yet, forgive them now.

28:56.738 --> 29:08.871
You imagine if you went into your Christmas gathering, like already with like just a pile of forgiveness and you're just like throwing it out at people as you idiot, here's some forgiveness, jerk, here's some forgiveness.

29:08.931 --> 29:11.974
I knew you were gonna do that, especially you, you know?

29:12.014 --> 29:15.237
You're just ready with like a bowl of forgiveness, you know?

29:15.938 --> 29:23.346
A reservoir, unstoppable, shalom, if you choose to forgive offenders ahead of time.

29:24.386 --> 29:25.167
What am I saying today?

29:25.207 --> 29:25.968
Here's what I'm saying.

29:26.008 --> 29:27.030
Here's my heart.

29:29.814 --> 29:40.088
Just because the baby came into the world, just because he's the prince of peace, just because he said peace and good well to all men, it doesn't mean that there's gonna be shalom in your heart and your family in relation.

29:40.108 --> 29:41.530
You have to work at this deal.

29:41.610 --> 29:42.592
Here's how I wrote it in your notes.

29:43.953 --> 29:45.516
If you want peace, you have to make it.

29:45.536 --> 29:47.218
Like you have to make it.

29:47.810 --> 29:49.052
You have to be flexible.

29:49.072 --> 29:50.695
You have to own the responsibility.

29:50.735 --> 29:52.237
You have to keep your mouth shut.

29:52.537 --> 29:53.519
Now is not the time.

29:53.759 --> 29:54.881
You have to forgive.

29:54.921 --> 29:56.864
You have to be kind.

29:56.884 --> 29:59.268
You have to create it and work towards it.

29:59.448 --> 30:00.971
If it's possible, here's what Paul said.

30:01.391 --> 30:05.558
If it's possible, as far as it depends on you, live at peace with everybody.

30:05.758 --> 30:06.560
Will you own that?

30:06.600 --> 30:07.020
Yes or no?

30:07.040 --> 30:07.801
Will you own that?

30:09.284 --> 30:11.107
Man, what would your holiday gathering look like?

30:12.469 --> 30:15.794
Something tells me there would just be a little bit more shalom.

30:17.026 --> 30:21.174
if you worked at being a peacemaker, a child of God.

30:22.757 --> 30:26.684
So here's my question to you as we close this up.

30:26.704 --> 30:29.430
Will you be a troublemaker or a peacemaker?

30:31.053 --> 30:32.115
Are you going to stir the pot?

30:32.135 --> 30:32.936
Are you going to gossip?

30:32.956 --> 30:34.259
Are you going to be easily offended?

30:34.279 --> 30:35.601
Are you going to be a blame shifter?

30:35.621 --> 30:36.824
Are you going to be a know-it-all?

30:37.565 --> 30:38.427
Are you going to be a volcano?

30:38.447 --> 30:39.128
Are you going to have a blow-up?

30:39.148 --> 30:40.210
Are you going to throw something?

30:42.306 --> 30:54.318
You're gonna be a Disturber of the Peace, or you're gonna bring peace, bring it, bring it, bring it to that family gallery, so that you can have Shalom, all the essential parts, the nieces, the nephews, the uncles, the cousins, the grandma, the grandpa, the husband, the wife.

30:54.678 --> 30:58.662
All the peace is working together well, so that there is peace in that home.

30:59.102 --> 31:00.784
You've gotta work at that, yes?

31:01.505 --> 31:02.305
This is a fair challenge?

31:04.568 --> 31:05.909
It's possible with God's help.

31:06.229 --> 31:09.753
It's the work he wants to create, and he's given us his spirit to do that.

31:09.773 --> 31:11.314
Today's baptism weekend.

31:12.002 --> 31:14.988
Baptism is a great picture of peacemaking.

31:15.509 --> 31:17.072
Somebody gets put under the water.

31:17.092 --> 31:20.639
The water symbolically washes them of their sin.

31:20.699 --> 31:25.970
They come back up a brand new person, reunited with God, forgiven.

31:26.010 --> 31:30.098
At peace, the Bible word is reconciled with God.

31:30.370 --> 31:32.513
They've died to their old way of living.

31:32.693 --> 31:36.439
They've come up to a brand new way of life, peace with God, life with God.

31:36.739 --> 31:38.021
We're about to baptize some folks.

31:38.041 --> 31:41.787
In fact, I'm going to baptize my nephew and my son today as well as many others.

31:42.728 --> 31:43.309
So exciting.

31:46.914 --> 31:49.839
Before we do that, before we do that, I want to share a story with you.

31:49.879 --> 31:52.603
Good friends of mine, Kevin and Casey Paulin.

31:53.464 --> 31:57.149
They have been on some wild journey with God in their life.

31:58.592 --> 32:00.274
And it's been like over a decade.

32:01.058 --> 32:06.506
and they've been through fighting cancer, addiction, lost a home, just so many different things.

32:06.526 --> 32:08.349
We couldn't even capture the whole entire story.

32:08.990 --> 32:10.552
But through the story, here's what they did.

32:10.632 --> 32:14.899
They never stopped seeking God.

32:16.681 --> 32:22.430
I'm sure they had moments, but they kept coming back and opening up their heart towards God.

32:22.510 --> 32:30.482
I want you to hear their story because it's a story of peace, peace internally for them, but then also peace between each other and peace.

32:30.946 --> 32:32.869
with God and they got baptized this weekend.

32:33.310 --> 32:34.852
Their names are Kevin and Casey Pollan.

32:34.932 --> 32:35.693
Check out their story.

32:38.978 --> 32:40.480
So I went to college to play baseball.

32:41.041 --> 32:46.409
I had a successful career, but during college, you know, I started having pains in my hips.

32:46.790 --> 32:54.161
They finally diagnosed me with a vascular necrosis, which is where the blood flow stops to the hips and the hip bone dies.

32:55.563 --> 32:58.147
So with that, I had to stop my baseball career.

32:58.568 --> 33:00.050
During that time, my parents

33:00.194 --> 33:04.320
got divorced and I really lost track of my identity.

33:04.941 --> 33:17.258
The pain was getting so bad that he did finally go to a doctor and they really wanted to hold off on any kind of hip replacement because of how young he was.

33:17.298 --> 33:22.906
That's when the addiction to the pain pills started.

33:22.926 --> 33:25.830
I didn't know I was an addict at the time.

33:26.511 --> 33:28.754
Once that first prescription hit, it just

33:29.058 --> 33:31.261
You know, it became more and more and more.

33:31.621 --> 33:38.090
You add on the alcohol to that and the anguish inside where I didn't know my identity.

33:38.110 --> 33:44.118
It really started to spiral out of control really fast.

33:45.140 --> 33:55.634
At that point, I felt like I was really protecting our children and keeping things covered up for them and making a lot of excuses why daddy was sleeping all the time.

33:56.098 --> 33:58.641
People on the outside didn't understand the pain I was going through.

33:58.701 --> 34:01.324
My own wife didn't know the struggle to get out of bed.

34:01.344 --> 34:07.390
It was a struggle to go to the mailbox, let alone play with, you know, an eight-year-old boy and a two-year-old daughter.

34:08.291 --> 34:09.172
It was too much.

34:09.232 --> 34:10.073
I had to do something.

34:10.093 --> 34:11.034
I wasn't working anymore.

34:11.094 --> 34:14.918
So I did go ahead and get my first hip replacement when my daughter was two.

34:15.499 --> 34:22.066
Things went OK for a while after that surgery until the other hip started really bothering me.

34:22.326 --> 34:25.650
So it started to cycle over again, more pain medicine, more

34:27.074 --> 34:29.798
more lies, more feeling, more shame.

34:31.000 --> 34:39.433
We were having a really big argument because pills were just missing and gone and it was just out of control.

34:39.693 --> 34:43.759
She was saying you're going to lose your family and I refused to see that.

34:43.839 --> 34:45.802
I thought I had control of the situation.

34:46.243 --> 34:56.338
And when he walked out the door, that was the moment I decided that it was time to take action and I packed up all of our clothes and the kids and I moved in with my mom.

34:56.898 --> 34:58.260
very difficult to deal with.

34:58.340 --> 34:59.522
I didn't know what to do.

34:59.823 --> 35:03.628
And again, I went to drugs and alcohol as a result.

35:04.370 --> 35:05.271
I knew it was selfish.

35:06.333 --> 35:08.155
I knew it was, but I still did it.

35:08.937 --> 35:09.838
I couldn't stop myself.

35:11.300 --> 35:14.946
Even though it was creating more of a wedge in our relationship.

35:15.367 --> 35:22.177
When things started really getting bad, I knew that I could come to a manual for counsel.

35:22.578 --> 35:25.362
I would come to the church

35:27.202 --> 35:41.957
and just sit and lay down in the back of my car and just cry and pray and ask God for direction on what to do because I just felt so lost.

35:42.718 --> 35:54.770
I got another month refilled from the doctor of pain medicine and that was gone in about a week and a half and that's when I had to make a decision of rehab or surgery.

35:55.266 --> 36:00.593
I did call my wife at that point, Casey, and we talked through it, and she talked to the doctor.

36:00.653 --> 36:04.978
I talked to the doctor, and the decision was made to do the surgery before rehab.

36:05.579 --> 36:08.222
I was reassuring him that this is it.

36:08.883 --> 36:10.665
You can start living your life again.

36:10.725 --> 36:13.528
You can be done with the pills.

36:14.169 --> 36:15.371
The surgery went great.

36:15.431 --> 36:19.476
His second hip replacement, it went great, and it all was going really, really well.

36:20.196 --> 36:24.722
Then the next day, out of nowhere, Kevin,

36:25.506 --> 36:29.232
started not feeling well and he started running a fever.

36:30.113 --> 36:31.936
The fever just continued to climb.

36:32.257 --> 36:40.410
That's when I left the room and just started walking around the hospital and chest was talking out loud.

36:41.091 --> 36:42.714
Like, why is this happening?

36:42.974 --> 36:46.219
God, what are we doing wrong?

36:47.000 --> 36:53.010
Literally, as soon as I asked that question, the word trust

36:54.882 --> 37:08.204
and it just came to me that I was putting all trust into myself and none of it into God.

37:08.224 --> 37:11.329
The next morning, the fever just disappeared.

37:11.950 --> 37:12.992
There's no explanation.

37:13.773 --> 37:14.995
They don't know why it happened.

37:15.015 --> 37:16.117
They don't know why it went away.

37:16.738 --> 37:18.781
But, you know, I got to go home that night.

37:19.963 --> 37:21.906
So, you know, to us, it's a miracle.

37:22.370 --> 37:30.558
You know, Kevin and I drove home and I got him settled in his bed and I went to run some errands before our kids were brought home to see him.

37:31.499 --> 37:40.008
I just turned off the radio and decided that I needed to just thank God and have this big conversation with him.

37:41.549 --> 37:50.578
And while I was talking to him, it just felt so good and free and literally I did feel the Holy Spirit.

37:51.938 --> 37:57.044
come over my entire body so much so that I had to pull over.

37:57.104 --> 38:01.189
And all I did was say, thank you so much.

38:02.731 --> 38:09.299
Thank you so much, God, for letting me know it's all gonna be okay and showing me that you are so real.

38:09.939 --> 38:18.770
And it was like, you need to go home and your kids need to come home and you need to stay there with him and it's going to be okay.

38:19.682 --> 38:22.927
And at that time, I knew that it was time to move back in.

38:22.947 --> 38:26.833
There was a lot of yelling that was going on in our house before this.

38:27.093 --> 38:31.940
And I made the decision that with God's help, I was no longer going to be yelling.

38:31.980 --> 38:35.746
And I was just going to put all my trust and faith in God.

38:35.766 --> 38:41.434
The doctors and Casey and I, we really worked on weaning me off the pain medicine.

38:41.754 --> 38:43.537
And we were able to do that successfully.

38:45.180 --> 38:46.181
Fantastic, right?

38:47.102 --> 38:49.586
Well, maybe not so much because

38:49.826 --> 38:54.572
drinking just started escalating and other drugs became present.

38:55.133 --> 38:59.879
There was a day where I was driving and I was intoxicated.

39:00.680 --> 39:06.548
Something came over me that said, you're gonna die or you're gonna kill somebody if you don't stop right now.

39:07.088 --> 39:11.815
And I pulled over at that moment and that's when I made the phone call to my best friend.

39:12.636 --> 39:17.522
He guided me to call Casey and you know reveal the truth to her and that's what we did.

39:18.402 --> 39:31.977
with the guidance of my friends and her and not knowing at the time, but it was God and the Holy Spirit led me to Fairbanks, drug and alcohol rehabilitation.

39:31.997 --> 39:35.762
And that's where I feel like I really turn the corner of my life.

39:35.782 --> 39:46.674
I feel like I have tools now, how to approach conflict, how to approach negative feelings inside without going to a substance.

39:47.106 --> 39:50.930
I don't try to make it go away myself because I'm not in charge anymore.

39:50.950 --> 39:54.914
I was never in charge, but I know now that I'm not in charge.

39:54.934 --> 39:55.835
God is in charge.

39:57.897 --> 40:09.970
When we started putting God first in our family is when our marriage became beyond amazing.

40:09.990 --> 40:13.874
The relationship between my children and I has grown stronger than ever.

40:13.986 --> 40:19.593
With Casey, you know, to be honest, the vulnerability has really strengthened our relationship.

40:20.854 --> 40:22.356
We're closer now than we've ever been.

40:22.917 --> 40:27.783
My relationship with God is so much stronger in any situation.

40:27.843 --> 40:29.084
God is where I go first.

40:30.566 --> 40:34.131
I wanted this to be real and not, not a show.

40:34.711 --> 40:41.920
This is my commitment to my family and God and that he's all powerful and he's leading the way.

40:41.940 --> 40:43.442
We got here together.

40:44.066 --> 40:46.691
at this moment as a family.

40:47.833 --> 40:53.344
We waited for one another to get baptized, and we all wanted to do it together.

40:58.794 --> 41:00.898
Today's a pretty good day, isn't it?

41:00.918 --> 41:01.579
That's not bad.

41:04.184 --> 41:05.266
You know, the video

41:05.538 --> 41:08.329
And the testimony is powerful enough, but we want to share something with you.

41:08.349 --> 41:09.213
It's pretty amazing.

41:09.233 --> 41:12.687
As of today, Kevin has been sober for four years.

41:13.048 --> 41:14.514
How cool is that?

41:19.362 --> 41:21.285
And for some of you today, man, you need that.

41:21.505 --> 41:22.227
You need to hear that.

41:22.267 --> 41:23.449
You need to hear that there's hope.

41:23.489 --> 41:27.275
You need to hear that that's the kind of God that we love and that's the kind of God that we serve.

41:27.295 --> 41:28.898
And that's how he can move in people's lives.

41:28.938 --> 41:29.939
Maybe you need to hear that.

41:30.440 --> 41:36.690
Maybe you needed to hear what Pastor Danny was talking about when he talked about peace, that the God that we love and the God that we serve is a God of peace.

41:36.750 --> 41:38.273
And we are called to be as ambassadors.

41:38.633 --> 41:42.380
We are called to be the peacemakers at the holiday time or any time.

41:42.420 --> 41:46.386
Any time we're interacting with anybody, we are called to bring peace just as God did.

41:46.466 --> 41:53.514
And maybe for you, seeing baptism serviced today was something that you needed to push you a little bit to take that next step in your faith.

41:53.554 --> 41:55.636
I don't know, maybe that's what you need.

41:56.136 --> 41:58.799
But for some of you, it's hard for you to experience this peace.

41:58.839 --> 42:01.983
It's difficult because there might be distance between you and God.

42:02.683 --> 42:03.805
And so you need to hear this today.

42:03.845 --> 42:05.306
And second Corinthians 5, 19.

42:06.407 --> 42:13.175
It says, for God was in Christ reconciling the world to himself.

42:13.575 --> 42:16.338
No longer counting people's sins against them.

42:16.834 --> 42:19.298
and you need to hear that because you think that you're too far gone.

42:20.119 --> 42:25.046
You think that the sins you've committed to your past will not allow you to have fellowship or relationship with him, but you are wrong.

42:25.667 --> 42:34.160
You might need to hear verse 21 where it says, for God made Christ who never sinned to be the offering for our sins so that we could be made right with God through Christ.

42:34.981 --> 42:40.109
If you want to experience that peace with God, then you have to go through Jesus and you need to hear that today.

42:40.149 --> 42:44.495
And I'm here to tell you that Jesus Christ lived a sinless, perfect life.

42:44.575 --> 42:46.418
He was absolutely perfect.

42:46.882 --> 42:50.429
But he chose to live his life as a servant.

42:50.489 --> 42:54.616
He chose to be a human being, to live right here with us, to forsake a home.

42:54.677 --> 42:56.881
He chose to live among us and to serve us.

42:58.003 --> 43:00.387
And he died for us to take the penalty of all sin.

43:01.229 --> 43:06.739
For the gluttony, the greed, the sloth, the wrath, the envy, the pride, the lust, the addiction, the alcoholism.

43:07.160 --> 43:10.386
Any sin you can think of, he took all of it.

43:11.394 --> 43:19.766
when he died and he rose again three days later, conquering the penalty of sin and death so that you could have a relationship with God the Father for all eternity.

43:19.826 --> 43:21.649
And some of you need to hear that today.

43:21.709 --> 43:25.715
And so some of you need to step into that relationship with him.

43:25.735 --> 43:27.598
You need to go to Jesus Christ right now.

43:28.159 --> 43:31.303
You need to ask him forgiveness of your sins and you need to align your life with him.

43:31.684 --> 43:32.585
I'm gonna tell you how to do that.

43:32.605 --> 43:34.508
You're gonna take my words, you're gonna make them your own.

43:35.069 --> 43:36.351
You're gonna pray this simple prayer.

43:36.411 --> 43:38.514
You go right to Jesus, nobody else.

43:38.850 --> 43:40.632
This is just about a moment between you and him.

43:40.672 --> 43:41.913
It's not about joining a manual.

43:42.134 --> 43:43.175
It's not about joining a church.

43:43.195 --> 43:44.256
It's not about joining a religion.

43:44.716 --> 43:48.260
It's about you having a relationship with Jesus Christ right now.

43:49.141 --> 43:51.364
So let's bow our heads and take these words and you make them your own.

43:55.308 --> 44:01.074
Jesus, I am so thankful for what you did for me on the cross.

44:03.457 --> 44:04.578
Jesus, you died for me.

44:06.601 --> 44:07.922
You paid the penalty.

44:08.226 --> 44:10.970
For my sin, you gave your life for me.

44:10.990 --> 44:15.837
And then you rose again, conquering the penalty of sin and death.

44:17.680 --> 44:19.783
And Jesus, I come to you begging for forgiveness.

44:20.844 --> 44:22.006
Forgive me of my sins.

44:22.066 --> 44:29.156
Wash me, cleanse me, and show me what it is to live a life with you.

44:30.238 --> 44:33.142
Show me what it is to live and experience a life of peace.

44:34.724 --> 44:35.986
Jesus, I'm yours forever.

44:37.122 --> 44:38.867
It is in your name, I only pray.

44:39.510 --> 44:39.871
Amen.

44:41.416 --> 44:44.646
Now if you prayed this prayer just now, they are celebrating in heaven.

44:44.686 --> 44:46.271
We want to celebrate with you right now.

44:46.672 --> 44:47.816
We are so happy for you.

44:47.876 --> 44:49.842
We would like.

44:51.490 --> 44:53.192
We would like to continue the celebration.

44:53.232 --> 44:55.134
We want to put a free gift in your hand.

44:55.154 --> 44:58.298
We want to put a New Believer's New Testament Bible in your hands.

44:58.318 --> 45:00.621
You can go visit our friends in the back at the New Believer's Table.

45:00.921 --> 45:02.263
If you're online, you just prayed this prayer.

45:02.283 --> 45:03.524
We are so excited for you.

45:03.965 --> 45:04.445
Let us know.

45:04.506 --> 45:05.507
Drop us a line in the comments.

45:05.527 --> 45:07.769
We will send this New Believer's New Testament for you.

45:07.789 --> 45:14.157
There is no better way for you to understand the will of God and how you can follow Him in each and every single way than to dive into this book.

45:14.197 --> 45:18.322
Can we give God a hand one more time for all the amazing things He is doing here?

